            <li><strong>Settings:</strong> Open Gmail → Click gear icon (⚙️) → "See all settings"</li>
            <li><strong>General:</strong> Go to the "General" tab</li>
            <li><strong>Signature:</strong> Scroll to "Signature" section → Click "Create new"</li>
            <li><strong>Name:</strong> Give your signature a name (e.g., "Professional")</li>
            <li><strong>Paste:</strong> In the editor, press <kbd>Ctrl+V</kbd> (or <kbd>Cmd+V</kbd> on Mac)</li>
            <li><strong>Save:</strong> Scroll down → Click "Save Changes"</li>
            <li><strong>Done!</strong> Your signature will appear in new emails automatically</li>
          </ol>
          <div style='margin-top: 16px; padding: 12px; background: rgba(102, 126, 234, 0.1); border-radius: 8px; font-size: 13px;'>
            💡 <strong>Pro Tip:</strong> You can set this signature to appear automatically in all new emails and replies!
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>
</Layout>

