          <ol class='list-decimal list-inside space-y-2 text-sm'>
            <li><strong>Copy:</strong> Click the "Copy Signature" button above</li>
            <li><strong>Settings:</strong> Open Gmail → Click gear icon → "See all settings"</li>
            <li><strong>General:</strong> Go to the "General" tab</li>
            <li><strong>Signature:</strong> Scroll to "Signature" section → Click "Create new"</li>
            <li><strong>Name:</strong> Give your signature a name (e.g., "Professional")</li>
            <li><strong>Paste:</strong> Click in the signature editor and press <kbd>Ctrl+V</kbd> (or <kbd>Cmd+V</kbd> on Mac)</li>
            <li><strong>Verify:</strong> You should see the formatted signature (not HTML code)</li>
            <li><strong>Save:</strong> Scroll down → Click "Save Changes"</li>
            <li><strong>Done:</strong> Your signature will appear in new emails automatically</li>
          </ol>
          <div style='margin-top: 16px; padding: 12px; background: #f0f9ff; border: 1px solid #bfdbfe; border-radius: 6px; font-size: 13px; color: #1e40af;'>
